<p><span style="font-size: 22px;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The internet is full of plans that aim to help you lose weight quickly. Some require a controlled diet, others require eating at fixed hours. But does losing weight mean that you automatically lose fat or inches around your waist? There is a clear difference scientific between weight loss vs fat loss, which is what we are outlining below.</span> <br /></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 22px;"><span style="font-size: 26px; font-weight: bold;">What Is Weight Loss?</span><br /></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 22px;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Weight loss is a decrease in your overall body weight. This weight includes muscle, fat, and water in your body.</span><br /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 26px;">What Is Fat Loss?<br /></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 26px;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="font-size: 22px;">Here’s the main difference between weight loss and fat loss: fat loss refers to weight loss from fat, and it’s a more specific and healthful goal than weight loss. Most of the time, when we talk about wanting to lose weight, we’re really talking about wanting to lose fat. This is not only because excess fat is potentially dangerous but also because you don’t want to get rid of lean tissue.</span><br /></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 26px;"><span style="font-size: 22px;"><br /></span></span></p>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img style="max-width: 80%;" src="data:image/png;base64," /></div>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 26px;">Weight Loss Vs Fat Loss</span><br /></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 26px;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 22px;">The weight loss vs fat loss difference requires deeper discussion. Fat loss is more specific than weight loss. We can lose body fat by reducing calories, just like with weight loss. The quality of food we consume for fat loss, vs weight loss, is more important. We need to be more specific about our macronutrient intake, i.e. protein, carbohydrate and fat intake.</span><br /></span></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 26px;"><span style="font-size: 22px;"><br /></span></span></p>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img style="max-width: 80%;" src="data:image/png;base64," /></div>
<p><span style="font-size: 22px;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The goal to successful weight loss vs fat loss is to preserve as much muscle as possible, or possibly even gain some, while at the same time lose as much body fat as possible. Your body fat percentage is a key indicator of your success, not the scale. In fact, stay off the scale.</span> <br /></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 22px;"><span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 26px;">The Focus: Fat Loss, Not Weight Loss</span><br /></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 22px;"><span style="font-size: 26px;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 22px;">In the battle of weight loss vs fat loss, you should focus on fat loss. Most weight loss programs will help you lose weight - but much of it will be in the form of water and muscle. And as we mentioned above, real success in keeping the kilos off for good lies in preserving muscle while doing away with fat. That’s why it is important to understand the difference between weight loss vs fat loss and eat a diet and follow a regimen that helps keep fat off.</span><br /></span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 22px;"><span style="font-size: 26px;"><span style="font-size: 22px;"><br /></span></span></span></p>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img style="max-width: 80%;" src="data:image/png;base64," /></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 26px;">Why You Need To Maintain Healthy Muscle Mass</span><br /></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 26px;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 22px;">Losing muscle has detrimental effects, because losing weight in the form of muscle can lower the number of calories you burn at rest, making it easier to regain any weight you may have lost as fat. The more muscle you have, the more calories you burn while resting.</span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 26px;"><span style="font-size: 22px;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Maintaining a healthy percentage of muscle has numerous benefits, such as:</span><br /></span></p>
<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; <span style="font-size: 20px;">*&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 20px;">Maintaining healthy fat levels in the blood (triglycerides and cholesterol)</span><br /></p>
<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="font-size: 20px;">&nbsp; &nbsp; *&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 20px;">Regulating healthy blood sugar levels</span><br /></p>
<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="font-size: 20px;">&nbsp; &nbsp; *&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 20px;">Controlling inflammation</span><br /></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 20px;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="font-size: 22px;">Several studies have linked a higher fat-to-muscle ratio to chronic diseases like metabolic syndrome, heart disease, and diabetes). It also lowers your risk of age-related muscle loss, which can lead to certain disabilities.</span><br /></span></p>
<p><br /></p>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img style="max-width: 80%;" src="data:image/png;base64," /></div>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 26px;">How To Lose Fat While Retaining Muscle</span><br /></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 26px;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 22px;">In the battle of weight loss vs fat loss, the key is losing the flab while retaining (and even building) muscle. There are a few simple ways to ensure you’ll lose weight in the form of fat and either maintain or gain muscle mass:</span><br /></span></p>
<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 24px; text-decoration-line: underline;">Protein</span><span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 24px;">:</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 22px;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Protein is an important nutrient for everyone (not just athletes and bodybuilders), and a key component of fat loss. That doesn’t mean you need to start drinking protein shakes every day. Most people can get the protein they need from a healthy and balanced diet. Protein is essential to building bones and plays a part in metabolic reactions, immune response, assists in cellular repair, forms blood cells, and more.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 22px;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Protein is also important for maintaining the muscle you have and supporting new muscle growth, especially when losing weight. A high-protein diet reduces hunger, helping you eat fewer calories. The recommended dietary allowance for protein is 0.8-1.2 grams per kg of body weight per day.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 22px;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /></span></p>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img style="max-width: 80%;" src="data:image/png;base64," /></div>
<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration-line: underline; font-size: 24px;">Carbohydrates</span><span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 24px;">:</span><br /></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 24px;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 22px;">However, prioritising protein at meals doesn’t mean cutting out the carbs. Breaking up with entire food groups isn’t a must for losing fat, and it’s definitely not a good move for keeping the fat off long-term.
</span><br /></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 24px;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="font-size: 22px;">Research suggests that healthy, sustainable weight loss really happens from eating a wide variety of wholesome foods like fruit and veggies, whole grains, and lean proteins and limiting the processed, sugary stuff.</span><br /></span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration-line: underline; font-size: 24px;"><br /></span></p>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img style="max-width: 80%;" src="data:image/png;base64," /></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: bold;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration-line: underline; font-size: 24px;">Exercise</span><span style="font-size: 24px;">:</span></span><br /></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 24px;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 22px;">Exercise is the most effective way to encourage fat loss without losing muscle. Combining exercise with a higher protein intake can help get better results. One must get at least 150 minutes of exercise per week. It is important to keep up the metabolism and prevent muscle loss.</span><br /></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 24px;"><span style="font-size: 22px;"><br /></span></span></p>
